</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,295,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="495">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[364,509,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Duplachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[364,509,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="495">D. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded on sugarcane in 
<collectingRegion box="[819,1000,1087,1112]" country="Colombia" name="Valle del Cauca" pageId="5" pageNumber="495">Valle del Cauca</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lastra" box="[1048,1326,1088,1112]" pageId="5" pageNumber="495" refString="Lastra, L. A. &amp; Gomez, L. A. (1997) Observaciones del ciclo de vida de la escama blanca Duplachionaspis divergens (Green) (Homoptera: Diaspididae) y reconocimiento de enemigos naturales. In: Congreso de la Asociacion Colombiana de Tecnicos de la Cana de Azucar, Tecnicana. 4 Memorias. Cali, Colombia. pp. 41 - 52." type="journal article" year="1997">Lastra &amp; Gómez (1997)</bibRefCitation>
were not available in the present study. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lastra" box="[643,914,1124,1148]" pageId="5" pageNumber="495" refString="Lastra, L. A. &amp; Gomez, L. A. (1997) Observaciones del ciclo de vida de la escama blanca Duplachionaspis divergens (Green) (Homoptera: Diaspididae) y reconocimiento de enemigos naturales. In: Congreso de la Asociacion Colombiana de Tecnicos de la Cana de Azucar, Tecnicana. 4 Memorias. Cali, Colombia. pp. 41 - 52." type="journal article" year="1997">Lastra &amp; Gómez (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, the identification of 
<taxonomicName box="[1153,1296,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Duplachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[1153,1296,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="495">D. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was done in the 
<collectingCountry box="[196,255,1160,1184]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="495">USA</collectingCountry>
, but at the Colombian Center for Sugarcane Research (Cenicaña) there are no voucher specimens to support that identification (Dr. Germán Vargas, Cenicaña, personal communication, 2015).
</paragraph>
